      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAMBO'S ETHICS (8) boasts a consistent overall record including nine wins from 18 starts, but missed the frame latest when fourth (22.80) over 400m at Maitland. Strike rate this course strong having won five of nine tries. Boxed wide but will go close with the right run. CHA CHA ETHICS (2) has shown good improvement at her last two starts, hitting the frame latest when 2nd at Maitland over 400m. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Racing well and deserves a win. BRIMSON BANNER (7) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by 1.75 lengths at this track in a handy 17.51 beating Tarawi Tank. Has a solid record from this box including three wins and a minor placing. Expecting another bold showing. DESPICABLE LEO (1) should be thereabouts.",
